ngines\": { \"node\": \">=21\" }` (or `>=24` to match the `.ts`-import requirement) so the runtime contract is explicit.\n- **`conversion.ts:39` — `safePct` does not guard a non-finite/negative `numerator`** — it clamps the result to 0 so output is still safe, but a `Number.isFinite(numerator)` guard would make the helper symmetric and self-documenting. Minor.\n\n### Notes\n- The documented >100% clamping (hides genuinely dirty data) is a known, accepted trade-off with a deferred follow-up ADR — **not** re-flagged as a defect, consistent with the ADR.\n- `allowImportingTsExtensions: true` is correctly paired with `noEmit` (Next bundler) and `.ts`-extension imports confined to test files. No leak into app code (FunnelCard uses extensionless `../lib/conversion`).\n\n---\n## Verdict: **APPROVE**\nNo critical, security, or correctness issues. Three Low-severity quality notes above are non-gating and may be addressed in a follow-up. Review completed fully — nothing blocked.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

